subSubSection.paragraph:
Sternite preceding the SGP (VII): bearing a process on the anterior margin of the sternite, directed backwards; longer than the SGP length (
Fig. 8D, E
); the base of the process is weakly sclerotized; the apex of the process is sclerotized, forms a plate with moderately converging borders, and with a triangular notch on the apex; the subgenital plate is wider than longer, triangular, with a triangular notch on the apex.
